WEBVTT

00:02.377 --> 00:04.993
NARRATOR: Chester's Mill is a place
like any other.

00:05.172 --> 00:07.003
At least, it used to be,

00:07.174 --> 00:09.039
until we were cutoff
from the rest of the world

00:09.218 --> 00:10.879
by a mysterious dome.

00:15.098 --> 00:18.932
Invisible, indestructible,
inescapable.

00:19.102 --> 00:20.933
We're trapped.

00:21.104 --> 00:23.595
We don 't know where it came from
or why it's here,

00:23.774 --> 00:25.890
but now that we ’re all trapped
under the dome together,

00:26.068 --> 00:27.649
none of our secrets are safe.

00:27.819 --> 00:29.901
[SCREAMING]

00:30.072 --> 00:31.403
Thanks for letting me crash here.

00:31.573 --> 00:34.064
My husband isn't here,
but he'll turn up.

00:34.243 --> 00:35.653
- You'll see, Barbie.
PETER: Shut up!

00:37.329 --> 00:39.536
PAUL:
That thing is never gonna go away.

00:41.625 --> 00:42.910
LINDA:
Oh, no. No.

00:44.253 --> 00:46.289
The pink stars are falling in lines.

00:48.131 --> 00:49.257
BOY:
Do it.

00:52.302 --> 00:54.793
- Ride that dome.
GIRL: Nice.

00:56.848 --> 00:59.635
BOY 2: Whoa, Benny.
Dome ride was sick, bro.

01:00.477 --> 01:01.717
- Yeah.
PAUL [ON VIDEO]: It won't be okay.

01:01.895 --> 01:04.307
This thing is never gonna go away,

01:04.481 --> 01:06.096
and we ’re all gonna die.

01:06.275 --> 01:07.981
[GUNSHOTS ON VIDEO]

01:09.403 --> 01:10.984
Dude, you're watching that video
again?

01:11.863 --> 01:12.989
JOE:
I still can't believe it.

01:13.156 --> 01:16.444
DAN: You weren't kidding about that
Barbie. He took that cop's ass down.

01:16.618 --> 01:18.654
lwonder if Barbie's, like, Black Ops.

01:18.829 --> 01:21.161
- Oh, my God, your phone still works?
- So jealous.

01:21.331 --> 01:24.448
Yeah, the camera and the apps.
Just no texting or calls.

01:24.918 --> 01:25.998
I miss texting.

01:26.169 --> 01:29.127
- It's been, like, a day and a half.
- Whatever. Don't be judge-y.

01:29.965 --> 01:31.751
Dude. Show them.

01:31.925 --> 01:33.756
PAUL:
--is never gonna go away,

01:33.927 --> 01:36.304
- and we 're all gonna die.
LINDA: Paul, don’t.

01:37.347 --> 01:40.214
GIRL 2: The bulletjust bounced
off the dome.

01:41.518 --> 01:44.009
- Did Paul mean to shoot Freddy?
- I don't know.

01:44.187 --> 01:45.927
He was acting pretty crazy.

01:46.106 --> 01:49.394
- I wonder what they'll do with him.
- Cop killer's as bad as it gets.

01:49.568 --> 01:51.854
Especially a cop
that kills another cop.

01:58.660 --> 02:00.571
You in a hurry or something?

02:00.746 --> 02:03.613
I wanna get to the police station
before they walk Randolph in.

02:04.041 --> 02:06.248
What, you don't like my driving?

02:06.418 --> 02:08.784
Not that at all. Just...

02:09.838 --> 02:12.580
Nothing wrong
with using a little caution.

02:13.634 --> 02:14.714
I don't do caution.

02:14.885 --> 02:17.592
Heh. I noticed.

02:17.763 --> 02:20.505
You're a real run-towards-the-fire
kind of girl, aren't you?

02:20.682 --> 02:22.593
I'm a journalist.

02:22.768 --> 02:25.555
I've gotta find out all I can
about this dome.

02:25.729 --> 02:29.438
80 me, you and everyone in this town
can get out as soon as possible.

02:30.442 --> 02:33.275
I got a husband out there
I'd kind of like to see again.

02:42.204 --> 02:44.445
MAN 1: There he is.
MAN 2: There he is.

02:44.623 --> 02:46.454
- Deputy Esquivel.
WOMAN: Is that him?

02:46.625 --> 02:48.115
That was a pretty daring thing
you did,

02:48.293 --> 02:49.908
pulling Reverend Coggins
out of the fire.

02:50.087 --> 02:51.372
Just doing my job.

02:51.546 --> 02:53.082
So what,
with the entire Fire Department

02:53.256 --> 02:55.167
and half the police force
stuck outside the dome

02:55.342 --> 02:57.549
- and now two officers dead--
- What's your question?

02:57.719 --> 03:00.961
Can you handle this alone
until we find a way to get out?

03:02.057 --> 03:04.139
We'll be fine, Mrs. Shumway.

03:04.935 --> 03:06.926
As long as we all look out
for each other.

03:08.271 --> 03:09.477
- Murderer!
WOMAN 2: Killer!

03:09.648 --> 03:10.683
MAN 3: Yeah!
MAN 4: Let's get him!

03:10.857 --> 03:13.143
Any more of that,
and I'll haul your ass in.

03:13.318 --> 03:15.434
Hey, it was the dome
that did it to Freddy.

03:15.612 --> 03:17.318
And it's gonna kill more
before it's done.

03:17.489 --> 03:19.696
Take him inside. I can control this.

03:19.950 --> 03:21.315
Oh, so you're in charge now?

03:22.119 --> 03:23.484
Fﬂends,

03:23.662 --> 03:26.153
I'm asking you all
to let the law do its job.

03:26.331 --> 03:28.617
The law did its job already.
Killed an innocent man.

03:28.792 --> 03:31.204
No,no,no.
That was a tragic accident.

03:31.378 --> 03:32.959
As the town's only remaining
councilman,

03:33.130 --> 03:36.714
I will not countenance
any kind of frontierjustice.

03:38.009 --> 03:41.467
Now, you go home, clasp hands

03:41.763 --> 03:44.675
and pray for Freddy Denton's
poorsouL

03:45.016 --> 03:46.472
Go on.

03:52.858 --> 03:55.691
DAN: Too bad we can't upload
that video to YouTube.

03:55.861 --> 03:59.820
Excuse me. Where can a girl
charge up in this town?

04:00.991 --> 04:04.233
- I have a generator at my--
- Your house?

04:05.954 --> 04:07.785
DAN:
We saw you at the fire.

04:08.206 --> 04:09.241
How'd you end up here?

04:09.416 --> 04:11.873
I just followed some kids.
Heard them talking about a bonfire.

04:12.043 --> 04:13.783
- No, I meant--?
NORRIE: I knew what you meant.

04:13.962 --> 04:16.749
I was on my way someplace and:

04:17.090 --> 04:18.921
Wrong place at the wrong time,
Iguess.

04:20.343 --> 04:22.504
I'm not usually a mooch,
but without my music,

04:22.679 --> 04:25.466
I can get a little,
you know, super bitchy.

04:25.640 --> 04:27.255
Can I refuel at your place?

04:27.434 --> 04:29.641
Sure. There's no one home
except me--

04:29.811 --> 04:31.142
Cool.

04:31.313 --> 04:33.770
I actually need a place to crash too.

04:34.107 --> 04:35.187
If that's okay, I mean.

04:35.400 --> 04:38.608
Oh, well, I mean,
I saw you with two ladies,

04:38.779 --> 04:40.235
I thought you were with them.

04:40.405 --> 04:42.066
NORRIE:
Never seen them before.

04:43.074 --> 04:44.484
So...

04:45.160 --> 04:46.525
...cool to crash?

04:51.917 --> 04:53.202
PAUL:
I'm sorry.

04:53.376 --> 04:56.834
Freddy, he was my partner,
and he was my friend,

04:57.005 --> 04:59.587
but he wouldn't be dead
if it weren't for this dome.

05:00.008 --> 05:01.714
You're gonna have to tell Rusty.

05:02.677 --> 05:03.712
He'll understand.

05:03.887 --> 05:05.718
Like hell he will.
He's Freddy's brother.

05:05.889 --> 05:07.754
What did we do to deserve this?

05:11.019 --> 05:12.520
Are you okay?

05:12.687 --> 05:14.143
Paul?

05:17.526 --> 05:19.062
[GRUNTING]

05:24.908 --> 05:26.648
I warned you, Linda.

05:26.827 --> 05:28.237
I warned you what would happen.

05:28.411 --> 05:31.369
- This is all a misunderstanding, Paul.
- No, it's not.

05:31.540 --> 05:33.030
It's the dome.

05:33.208 --> 05:35.995
It's making everyone crazy,
and it's gonna kill us all,

05:36.169 --> 05:37.750
if the town doesn't kill me first.

05:39.297 --> 05:40.673
Paul?

05:40.841 --> 05:42.422
Paul!

06:04.114 --> 06:05.354
[SNIFFS]

06:06.116 --> 06:08.528
- Where were you yesterday, Junior?
- Nowhere.

06:11.329 --> 06:14.287
Whole town pulls together
to put out a fire.

06:14.457 --> 06:16.163
Butyou?

06:16.835 --> 06:19.497
Nowhere to be found.

06:19.796 --> 06:21.161
- Dad--
- Shut your mouth.

06:23.174 --> 06:26.541
People are looking to me to lead,

06:26.720 --> 06:28.961
to stand up like a man does.

06:29.139 --> 06:33.803
It reflects poorly
when my son is AWOL.

06:33.977 --> 06:37.845
This situation, it's an opportunity.

06:38.148 --> 06:40.890
All your life,
I've provided you with advantages.

06:41.067 --> 06:43.683
Opening doors,
like with the football team.

06:43.862 --> 06:44.897
I never wanted to play--

06:45.071 --> 06:47.733
Point is you only get
so many chances in life.

06:47.908 --> 06:49.364
Do not squander them.

06:52.954 --> 06:54.490
What happened to your face?

06:54.664 --> 06:56.450
- Nothing.
- No, what...?

07:00.253 --> 07:01.538
Who did this to your face?

07:02.839 --> 07:04.625
This guy.

07:04.799 --> 07:07.711
His name's Barbie, I think.

07:08.011 --> 07:09.842
He's totally insane.

07:11.473 --> 07:13.589
Nine years it's been
since your mother died,

07:15.477 --> 07:18.685
and still it's like you're hiding
behind her skirt.

07:21.107 --> 07:23.644
Best toughen up now, Junior.

07:25.695 --> 07:27.686
Don't you let me down.

07:33.870 --> 07:37.658
PHIL [OVER RADIO]: Your dial’s set to
WYBS, literally the only

07:37.832 --> 07:41.199
source of news here in Chester's Mill.
Couple of shout-outs.

07:41.378 --> 07:43.539
First, to everyone
who grabbed a bucket yesterday

07:43.713 --> 07:47.501
and joined the volunteer brigade,
way to stay civic-minded, people.

07:47.676 --> 07:49.883
And big ups
to the lovely Linda Esquivel

07:50.053 --> 07:51.213
[CLATTERING]

07:51.388 --> 07:53.504
for her daring rescue
of Reverend Coggins.

08:06.361 --> 08:08.397
I made you some eggs.

08:09.447 --> 08:11.779
Figured you could use some protein.

08:21.751 --> 08:23.582
I get it.

08:25.422 --> 08:27.538
You're angry,

08:28.258 --> 08:31.591
but it's the dome
that's making you act like this.

08:31.970 --> 08:34.928
Nothing's making me act like this.

08:36.516 --> 08:38.723
It's you locking me down here
for two days.

08:38.893 --> 08:43.933
Everything is gonna go back
to the way it was before.

08:44.482 --> 08:45.983
You'll see, Ange.

08:46.693 --> 08:49.685
Soon as we get out
from under this thing.

08:55.535 --> 08:57.526
Has anyone tried going under it?

08:57.704 --> 08:59.444
People took shovels
and tried digging--

08:59.622 --> 09:03.456
No, I mean, way under it.

09:03.626 --> 09:05.412
Like through the cement-factory
tunnels.

09:06.171 --> 09:08.958
They closed those off

09:09.132 --> 09:12.124
after the flood when those kids died
down there. It's dangerous.

09:12.302 --> 09:14.634
You and I still went down there
all the time.

09:15.138 --> 09:17.424
Walked through the tunnels

09:17.599 --> 09:21.137
till we came across the town line
into Westlake,

09:21.394 --> 09:22.975
hitchhiked back.

09:25.148 --> 09:27.309
Maybe you're right.

09:28.693 --> 09:30.308
Maybe

09:31.112 --> 09:34.149
things would be different
if you could find a way out.

09:39.120 --> 09:43.113
Maybe we could start over.

09:49.047 --> 09:50.503
I'll be back later.

10:02.977 --> 10:05.434
Rise and shine, Reverend.

10:06.147 --> 10:07.853
What the hell were you thinking?

10:08.024 --> 10:09.855
I told you to find the evidence
and destroy it,

10:10.026 --> 10:11.562
not torch a dead-man's house.

10:11.736 --> 10:13.601
I did what you told me.

10:13.780 --> 10:16.567
Found the bills of sales of propane,
set them on fire.

10:16.741 --> 10:19.198
All the evidence destroyed,
just like you asked.

10:19.369 --> 10:20.654
Listen up, Lester.

10:21.121 --> 10:25.285
Now, the only files left that can
implicate us in this drug business

10:25.542 --> 10:27.373
are right here.

10:28.086 --> 10:32.671
So we have to trust each other
on the security of those.

10:35.593 --> 10:39.336
Scoot on back to the mortuary and
take care of Freddy Denton's corpse.

10:40.849 --> 10:44.842
So, what are the odds
that you just passing through,

10:45.019 --> 10:48.432
happen to be here on the day
that an unprecedented,

10:48.606 --> 10:50.938
possibly supernatural event
occurred?

10:51.109 --> 10:53.725
God, I swear, you ask more questions
than anybody I've ever met.

10:53.903 --> 10:56.064
Well, you know you're pretty good
at evading them.

10:56.239 --> 10:58.070
And asking questions is my job.

10:58.241 --> 11:00.857
That's just your way of keeping people
from asking you anything.

11:01.161 --> 11:03.447
All right. Your turn.

11:03.621 --> 11:05.657
How does someone
as ambitious as you

11:05.832 --> 11:07.413
end up here in Chester's Mill?

11:08.126 --> 11:10.242
My husband grew up here.

11:10.712 --> 11:14.580
And circumstances shifted

11:14.757 --> 11:18.045
and it just made sense for us,

11:18.219 --> 11:20.756
you know, to come here
and start over.

11:27.478 --> 11:29.810
That's our DJ, Phil.

11:30.690 --> 11:32.226
- You wanna meet him?
- Uh, no.

11:32.400 --> 11:37.144
I mean, you guys gotta do work.
I'm gonna get a bite to eat at the diner.

11:39.699 --> 11:41.439
JIM:
Linda? Where are you?

11:41.951 --> 11:43.407
Jim. Jim!

11:43.578 --> 11:46.285
Jim, I'm down here! The keys.

11:49.250 --> 11:50.626
Where's Paul Randolph?

11:50.793 --> 11:52.954
He escaped.

11:54.339 --> 11:55.579
Linda? I'd hoped you were ready

11:55.757 --> 11:57.713
for the responsibility
of running this department.

11:57.884 --> 11:59.545
With all respect,
I don't need a lecture.

11:59.719 --> 12:02.677
Take a pause. We have
a disturbed fugitive on the loose.

12:02.847 --> 12:06.135
As councilman,
it is my job to organize a search party.

12:06.476 --> 12:10.310
Then go do it. But I'm not gonna wait
for someone else to get hurt.

12:12.398 --> 12:13.478
Damn it, Paul.

12:13.650 --> 12:15.106
- He took a rifle.
- Where you going?

12:15.276 --> 12:16.937
Black Ridge Woods.
He likes to hunt there.

12:17.570 --> 12:19.356
- Listen to me. It's too risky--
- Jim,

12:19.530 --> 12:22.863
I know you like to control things,
but you do not control me.

12:26.287 --> 12:29.700
Why worry? I bet they got government
scientists tapping on that thing,

12:29.874 --> 12:32.411
trying to figure out
how to talk with us in here.

12:32.877 --> 12:35.038
Maybe they'll figure out
how to get us more bacon.

12:35.213 --> 12:38.501
Bacon's the least of our worries,
Roger.

12:39.259 --> 12:41.716
Any sign of your daughter?

12:41.886 --> 12:43.717
Not since last night.

12:43.888 --> 12:46.345
Alice is out looking for her.

12:47.225 --> 12:50.843
I can't help but think that
it's just another one of those seizures

12:51.020 --> 12:53.978
and Norrie's laying unconscious
on the side of a road somewhere.

12:54.148 --> 12:55.979
ROSE:
Oh, now, I'm sure she's fine.

13:00.196 --> 13:01.857
Excuse me, sir.

13:02.031 --> 13:04.408
You wouldn't, by any chance,
have seen my daughter?

13:06.661 --> 13:08.697
Your daughter? How's that work?

13:09.956 --> 13:12.823
My partner and I
are a same-sex couple with a child.

13:13.876 --> 13:15.912
Welcome to the 2lst century.

13:16.087 --> 13:18.794
What are you doing here
in Chester's Mill anyway?

13:18.965 --> 13:21.798
We got stuck here
on our way to drop Norrie,

13:21.968 --> 13:25.051
our daughter,
our legitimate daughter,

13:25.346 --> 13:27.337
off to a nearby private school.

13:27.598 --> 13:30.089
Oh, the girl's reformatory, you mean.

13:31.853 --> 13:33.593
Think they can pray the gay
out of her?

13:34.230 --> 13:38.223
Why don't you come with me, honey?
Let's get you a cup of coffee.

13:39.068 --> 13:41.059
Authorities outside
still don't know the composition

13:41.237 --> 13:42.898
or the origin of the dome.

13:43.072 --> 13:46.314
Presumably they'll keep at it
until they get some answers.

13:46.576 --> 13:47.907
[ROCKSONG
PLAYING ON RECORD]

13:48.077 --> 13:50.489
I like this symbiotic thing
we got going on, man.

13:50.663 --> 13:53.325
Key to a civilized society
is a well-informed public.

13:53.499 --> 13:54.875
Oh, that and indoor plumbing.

13:55.251 --> 13:57.708
Oh, I forgot about indoor plumbing.

13:57.879 --> 14:00.495
- Fingers crossed that holds out.
- Heh, heh.

14:02.383 --> 14:04.999
JULIA: Where's Junior off to
in such a hurry?

14:06.179 --> 14:09.216
PHIL: I don't know.
It's the councilman's kid, though.

14:09.390 --> 14:11.597
If anyone's got the inside scoop,
it's him.

14:16.022 --> 14:17.728
Junior.

14:18.066 --> 14:21.479
- Where you headed?
- Just going for a hike.

14:21.652 --> 14:22.687
What's with the helmet?

14:22.862 --> 14:26.320
I don't have to answer your questions.
It's a free country.

14:32.580 --> 14:34.286
Thank you.

14:35.041 --> 14:38.454
- Do you mind?
- Hey, it's yourjoint.

14:38.878 --> 14:40.539
All mine, it seems.

14:40.797 --> 14:42.537
Had a girl, Angie,
working the lunch counter,

14:42.715 --> 14:46.003
but I haven't seen her
since Dome Day.

14:46.177 --> 14:49.340
So how's it been staying over
at Julia's? Nice and comfy?

14:51.974 --> 14:53.475
Small town, kiddo.

14:53.643 --> 14:55.349
It's only gonna get smaller.

14:57.021 --> 14:59.398
All right, listen up, people.
I got an announcement to make.

15:00.650 --> 15:04.063
Former Deputy Paul Randolph
has escaped police custody.

15:04.445 --> 15:05.901
Just as a precaution,

15:06.072 --> 15:09.439
I'm gonna ask you all to stay in your
homes until this situation is resolved.

15:09.617 --> 15:11.573
I'm also putting together
a search party,

15:11.744 --> 15:14.986
and I'm asking if any able-bodied men
are keen to join up.

15:15.164 --> 15:17.450
- Right here, Big Jim.
- Count me in too.

15:17.625 --> 15:20.492
All right.
Roger, Ollie, thank you much.

15:20.878 --> 15:23.164
Now, listen, boys, he's already
assaulted two other people,

15:23.339 --> 15:26.831
and he's stolen a mass of provisions
from Casper's Department Store.

15:27.009 --> 15:29.716
Now, he's on the run, but there's only
so many places he can hide.

15:30.263 --> 15:33.551
He took a rifle from the police station,
so bring your firearms.

15:36.394 --> 15:38.931
I don't believe
we've been formally introduced.

15:39.105 --> 15:42.597
I'm Jim Rennie.
People around here call me Big Jim.

15:43.401 --> 15:45.642
- Barbie.
- Barbie.

15:45.820 --> 15:49.563
Well, that's kind of a funny name for
a fella with your particular expertise.

15:52.869 --> 15:55.326
I saw you take that gun off Randolph
yesterday.

15:55.705 --> 15:58.162
What are you,
a bounty hunter or something?

15:58.332 --> 15:59.538
[CHUCKLES]

16:02.128 --> 16:03.743
Just kidding, of course.

16:03.921 --> 16:07.129
This Paul Randolph's
no fish in a barrel.

16:07.300 --> 16:09.962
He was a marine,
served two tours in Iraq.

16:10.136 --> 16:12.878
- Oh.
- Yeah. Won a Silver Star.

16:13.055 --> 16:14.670
Perfect.

16:16.058 --> 16:19.346
So, Barbie,

16:20.062 --> 16:21.973
you in or out?

16:27.528 --> 16:28.859
PHIL [OVER RADIO]:
This is Phil Bushey with an update

16:29.030 --> 16:32.147
concerning the ongoing manhunt
in town.

16:32.325 --> 16:34.111
Former Deputy Paul Randolph 's
squad car

16:34.285 --> 16:36.776
has been spotted off the road
at Black Ridge Woods.

16:37.246 --> 16:39.953
All Chester's Millers
are under an advisory

16:40.124 --> 16:43.537
to stay home
until the situation is resolved.

16:49.258 --> 16:51.169
Looks like he abandoned it.

16:53.429 --> 16:55.294
Oh, fellas,
I got something over here.

17:02.438 --> 17:03.974
Come on. This way.

17:06.108 --> 17:07.769
BARBIE:
Hey, hold on.

17:09.946 --> 17:12.278
This guy's got military training, right?

17:13.115 --> 17:16.073
That's a dummy trail, he'd never do
anything that obvious. Look at this.

17:16.744 --> 17:18.700
These branches here,
they're all broken.

17:18.871 --> 17:20.657
Right there.

17:22.583 --> 17:24.995
Our man came right through here.

17:31.259 --> 17:32.669
See, I knew you'd be useful.

18:56.218 --> 18:58.379
Do you always eat standing up?

18:58.554 --> 18:59.760
Animals eat standing up.

19:03.017 --> 19:05.133
Good point, Joe.
These are really good.

19:05.311 --> 19:07.802
They're, like, better than those
Amy's Breakfast Scramble Wraps

19:07.980 --> 19:10.938
- my moms buy at Whole Foods.
- Your moms?

19:11.901 --> 19:15.234
Yeah, my moms, my pops,
you know, like they say.

19:16.530 --> 19:18.566
- Where are your parents?
- Outside.

19:18.741 --> 19:21.733
My dad drives a rig,
so he's gone a lot,

19:21.911 --> 19:25.779
and my mom was in Westlake,
the next town over, when-- You know.

19:25.956 --> 19:27.617
What about yours?

19:28.250 --> 19:31.742
I was on my way to visit my dad
and, you know...

19:31.921 --> 19:33.331
He's a musician.

19:33.506 --> 19:35.747
But driving a rig's pretty cool too.

19:37.760 --> 19:39.375
Guess we're both unsupervised,
huh?

19:39.553 --> 19:40.588
DAN:
Hey, Joe-Joe.

19:44.183 --> 19:46.265
These two lovely ladies were hoping
to take advantage

19:46.435 --> 19:48.847
of your sweet, sweet
homemade electricity.

19:49.021 --> 19:51.728
- My family doesn't have a gennie.
GIRL 2: Mine, neither.

19:51.899 --> 19:55.483
And the music they play on WYBS
is, like, totally schizo.

20:00.700 --> 20:01.815
Did you invite anyone else?

20:02.284 --> 20:04.821
I might have mentioned the generator
to a few people.

20:04.995 --> 20:07.202
What about the whole
advisories-to-stay-inside thing?

20:07.373 --> 20:11.241
Dude, it's the apocalypse.
Advisories don't apply.

20:13.921 --> 20:15.161
Nice.

20:15.339 --> 20:16.499
Please tell me you hit that.

20:18.426 --> 20:21.338
Uncool, bro.
Leave a brother hanging.

20:44.869 --> 20:47.485
JIM:
Just like Butch and Sundance, huh?

20:48.748 --> 20:51.660
Are we the good guys
or the bad guys?

20:51.834 --> 20:53.950
You're military, aren't you?

20:54.211 --> 20:58.705
The way you disarmed Randolph
and the whole dummy-trail business.

20:58.883 --> 21:01.670
- No, I was just a grunt.
JIM: You were over there, weren't you?

21:02.511 --> 21:04.092
You ever been to war?

21:04.263 --> 21:06.845
No. Never had the privilege.

21:14.690 --> 21:15.770
[TWIG SNAPS]

21:17.693 --> 21:19.024
[GROANING]

21:23.073 --> 21:24.233
PAUL:
Hey!

21:24.408 --> 21:25.614
Next time, I'll aim higher!

21:31.540 --> 21:33.405
I'm warning you, guys,
you better leave me alone.

21:33.876 --> 21:35.662
I don't wanna hurt anyone else.

21:38.589 --> 21:40.170
[ROGER GROANING]

21:42.468 --> 21:46.381
Ollie, take Roger back to town before
that lunatic takes another pop at us.

21:50.017 --> 21:52.133
You and me,
we're finishing this thing.

21:53.687 --> 21:56.724
What's your objective here? To bring
him in or are we trying to take him out?

21:56.899 --> 21:59.231
Don't see it makes a difference
to a guy like you, does it?

22:00.069 --> 22:01.434
What, to a guy like me?

22:03.030 --> 22:05.521
We're losing the light. Let's move it.

22:25.344 --> 22:26.379
JUNIOR:
I found a way out.

22:51.203 --> 22:52.409
Don't.

23:00.379 --> 23:01.994
You shouldn't have followed me.

23:09.221 --> 23:10.882
Why did you come down here?

23:12.683 --> 23:15.140
I was just hoping
you'd find a way out.

23:16.061 --> 23:17.801
Sorry to let you down.

23:25.362 --> 23:26.772
I hate this thing.

23:30.492 --> 23:33.825
I hate you.

23:40.252 --> 23:42.334
[JUNIOR SCREAMING]

23:58.312 --> 24:01.349
Junior, are you okay?

24:01.523 --> 24:05.516
No. These tunnels are dangerous.
They're like a maze.

24:05.694 --> 24:07.730
How can you even find your way
out of the dark?

24:07.905 --> 24:10.362
They're even more dangerous
with this thing cutting into it.

24:10.950 --> 24:13.362
What if it collapses on us?

24:13.702 --> 24:15.567
People die in here.

24:15.746 --> 24:18.533
I did a story once on coal miners,

24:19.041 --> 24:21.498
guys trapped underground.

24:22.378 --> 24:24.039
You see the way the flame flickers?

24:25.214 --> 24:28.502
You know which way the air flows,
you follow it home.

24:30.761 --> 24:32.342
Let's go home.

24:45.859 --> 24:47.565
[RUSTLING]

24:50.239 --> 24:52.321
[OINKING]

24:59.331 --> 25:00.946
DAN:
Dude, you're not gonna believe this.

25:01.125 --> 25:03.332
The guys got The Simpsons Movie
going on a loop.

25:03.669 --> 25:05.751
They totally saw the dome coming.

25:05.921 --> 25:07.582
When can I ask people to leave?

25:08.382 --> 25:09.417
Scarecrow Joe.

25:10.175 --> 25:11.711
Nice house party, bro.

25:11.885 --> 25:14.171
Carter.
I used to go out with your sister.

25:14.346 --> 25:18.009
Well, stayed in more than we went out,
if you know what I mean. Heh, heh.

25:18.183 --> 25:21.926
Thanks for inviting us in, little man.
We'll just make ourselves at home.

25:22.146 --> 25:25.183
Think about it.
You have a house to yourself.

25:25.357 --> 25:27.894
You could become
the most popular guy in town.

25:28.068 --> 25:30.229
Maybe even get a girlfriend out of it.

25:32.865 --> 25:33.980
She digs you.

25:34.158 --> 25:36.365
I've got an instinct
about these things.

25:36.535 --> 25:39.242
Just don't tell her
about that funky seizure you had.

25:39.413 --> 25:41.779
Don't want her to think you're a spaz.

25:46.879 --> 25:48.460
Total spaz move.

25:48.630 --> 25:49.915
Let's work on that, dude.

25:50.466 --> 25:52.331
JULIA: Can you remember
which way we came?

25:52.509 --> 25:55.216
- I don't have a lot of matches left.
- Who cares?

25:55.387 --> 25:58.094
We're trapped down here,
we're trapped out there.

25:58.265 --> 26:00.130
What's the difference?

26:03.145 --> 26:05.386
I just wanted to do something
good today.

26:07.733 --> 26:09.473
A man stands up.

26:09.651 --> 26:11.187
A man doesn't screw up.

26:15.074 --> 26:17.360
We all screw up.

26:17.534 --> 26:20.150
We make bad choices.

26:20.746 --> 26:23.283
Tell that to my father.

26:25.667 --> 26:27.828
You wanna know how I ended up
in Chester's Mill?

26:28.295 --> 26:30.877
I was covering the mayor's race
in Chicago.

26:31.048 --> 26:35.382
The guy in the lead
was a real machine politician.

26:35.552 --> 26:37.804
I really wanted to take him down.

26:37.971 --> 26:40.257
About a week before the election,
one of my sources sent me

26:40.432 --> 26:43.219
some documents
that showed bribery.

26:43.393 --> 26:45.224
I thought the leaked docs
might be forged,

26:45.395 --> 26:47.431
but I went ahead with the story
anyway.

26:47.731 --> 26:49.722
And it blew up in my face.

26:49.900 --> 26:52.312
The truth about my little lie surfaced,

26:52.736 --> 26:54.852
the guy got reelected,

26:55.030 --> 26:58.397
and I was fired and disgraced.

27:01.245 --> 27:02.826
And now I'm here.

27:04.164 --> 27:06.405
So I know from screw-ups.

27:08.127 --> 27:10.209
Tell you one thing, though.

27:11.630 --> 27:13.666
I will never make that mistake again.

27:18.470 --> 27:20.756
We just keep moving forward.

27:20.931 --> 27:22.967
CARTER:
Who needs some juice?

27:23.767 --> 27:27.430
Whoa, hold up, freshie.
Five bucks for five minutes.

27:27.813 --> 27:29.678
Should I do something about this?

27:29.857 --> 27:33.020
Yeah, and get your face Picasso'd
by a guy who's got 25 pounds on you?

27:35.279 --> 27:36.689
He doesn't run our electricity.

27:36.864 --> 27:40.277
- Did you ever take American history?
- Uh, yeah.

27:40.450 --> 27:42.577
So you know about
the Sherman Antitrust Act?

27:42.744 --> 27:44.484
I don't know, maybe.

27:45.080 --> 27:48.572
Maybe not. Because if you had, you'd
know that what you're doing is illegal.

27:48.750 --> 27:50.126
Monopolies are illegal.

27:50.294 --> 27:54.287
Monopoly is not illegal.
We have the board game at my house.

27:54.464 --> 27:57.206
Well, then maybe you should go back
to your house.

27:58.010 --> 27:59.295
Play by yourself.

28:07.227 --> 28:09.218
I think I'd rather play with you, Red.

28:09.396 --> 28:11.887
- Why don't we take this upstairs?
- I think you should leave.

28:12.065 --> 28:13.930
Oh, I am leaving, little man.

28:14.109 --> 28:15.940
I'm going up to your sister's room.

28:16.111 --> 28:17.897
I don't think she'd mind,
I been there before.

28:18.071 --> 28:19.777
No, I want you to leave my house.

28:20.949 --> 28:24.282
Move, now, or this gets ugly fast.

28:27.289 --> 28:29.075
GIRL 1: The generator blew.
GIRL 2: Let's get out of here.

28:29.249 --> 28:30.910
This ain't even close to over,
scarecrow.

28:31.084 --> 28:32.620
[INDISTINCT CHATTERING]

28:35.047 --> 28:37.709
GIRL 2:
Let's go. It's done.

28:42.346 --> 28:44.177
How many matches do we have left?

28:44.640 --> 28:46.096
One.

28:49.144 --> 28:51.601
There's a reason for all this.

28:52.147 --> 28:56.015
The dome,
all those people who died.

28:56.485 --> 28:59.648
This all happened
when that Barbie guy showed up.

29:00.447 --> 29:02.779
Sometimes, when we don't understand
the answer to a thing,

29:02.950 --> 29:05.282
we look for someone to blame.

29:06.536 --> 29:08.151
Oh, I understand.

29:08.330 --> 29:11.322
I understand he attacked me
out of the blue.

29:12.834 --> 29:14.210
See this?

29:15.170 --> 29:16.876
You know how I got that?

29:17.631 --> 29:19.667
Good old Barbie.

29:19.841 --> 29:23.333
People think he's this hero,

29:23.679 --> 29:25.169
but he's a psychopath.

29:25.430 --> 29:28.422
Barbie just attacked you
for no reason?

29:28.850 --> 29:30.590
That's right.

29:32.020 --> 29:34.306
You don't know this guy.

29:34.856 --> 29:36.312
I mean, what's he really doing here?

29:37.359 --> 29:41.022
Has he been here before?
He has to answer some questions.

29:48.078 --> 29:50.194
What do we do now?

30:18.734 --> 30:21.692
JULIA:
Come on. I'll give you a ride home.

30:30.454 --> 30:33.116
BARBIE: I think we ought to call it a day
and get a fresh start tomorrow.

30:33.290 --> 30:34.871
Why, so we can give
Randolph a chance--?

30:35.042 --> 30:36.202
To get away?

30:36.376 --> 30:38.913
Come on, man, we're sealed in here.
Where the hell's he gonna go?

30:39.087 --> 30:40.418
I told you, we're finishing this.

30:40.589 --> 30:41.795
Why's that?

30:41.965 --> 30:45.753
So you can show the town
what a big man Big Jim is?

30:47.429 --> 30:49.841
You ever play football, Barbie?

30:51.600 --> 30:54.933
No. I was never much
of a team-sports kind of guy.

30:55.103 --> 30:56.354
[CHUCKLES]

30:56.521 --> 30:58.682
I played cornerback.

30:59.149 --> 31:04.018
A lot of smaller guys play it
because it requires speed and agility.

31:04.654 --> 31:08.943
Back in school,
we had this all-state wideout, a real...

31:09.117 --> 31:10.732
A real showboater, you know?

31:12.287 --> 31:15.279
He called me "Big Jim,"

31:15.457 --> 31:18.620
uh, but as a joke, you know?

31:18.794 --> 31:20.705
Laughing at me.

31:21.797 --> 31:25.130
And one day, we, um,
we had to scrimmage

31:25.300 --> 31:28.007
and he was taunting me, you know?

31:28.261 --> 31:30.126
"Come on, Big Jim," you know?

31:30.305 --> 31:33.297
"You can't touch me, Big Jim,"
you know?

31:38.563 --> 31:40.975
So I put the mother of all hits
on this punk.

31:41.149 --> 31:47.566
I mean, helmet first, went in low,
completely shattered his pelvis.

31:48.073 --> 31:49.404
Well, guess what.

31:50.492 --> 31:53.234
"Big Jim" wasn't a joke no more.

31:53.537 --> 31:55.243
What does that tell you?

31:56.039 --> 31:57.870
I don't know.
Tells me that being on your team

31:58.041 --> 31:59.577
could be hazardous to my health.

31:59.751 --> 32:02.868
Sometimes an example
needs to be made, you know?

32:03.255 --> 32:05.416
Command respect.

32:05.715 --> 32:07.330
An eye for an eye.

32:07.926 --> 32:09.507
[TWIG SNAPS]

32:11.555 --> 32:13.295
Jim?

32:14.766 --> 32:16.472
[RIFLE COCKS]

32:20.480 --> 32:23.142
I'll kill him
just like he was gonna kill me.

32:23.316 --> 32:26.103
- Nobody wants to kill anybody here.
- He said it himself.

32:26.278 --> 32:27.768
An eye for an eye, right?

32:29.281 --> 32:30.896
Make an example out of me.

32:31.783 --> 32:33.284
Drop your weapon now.

32:35.579 --> 32:37.115
I said, drop your weapon now.

32:37.289 --> 32:38.369
[GUNSHOT]

32:41.084 --> 32:42.494
[THUDS]

32:55.223 --> 32:56.679
JIM:
Evening to you, Lester.

32:56.850 --> 32:58.761
I'm sorry to say
we brought you another customer.

32:58.935 --> 33:00.926
I'm not finished
with Deputy Denton yet.

33:01.104 --> 33:02.685
Patching a wound takes time.

33:02.856 --> 33:05.472
Paul Randolph needs your help too.

33:05.734 --> 33:09.101
The Lord never gives us
more than we can handle, Rev.

33:10.030 --> 33:11.395
[DOOR OPENS]

33:11.865 --> 33:13.480
You clean?

33:13.658 --> 33:15.398
Absolutely, Jim.

33:15.577 --> 33:18.114
Any red you see in my eyes,
that's overwork, nothing else.

33:18.538 --> 33:20.278
Let's keep it that way.

33:25.420 --> 33:28.503
Would you mind waiting at the car?
I need to talk to Linda.

33:28.673 --> 33:30.789
Yeah. Sure.

33:33.053 --> 33:34.918
I'm sorry.

33:35.931 --> 33:40.095
For questioning your dedication,
or if in any way I insinuated

33:40.268 --> 33:42.975
that you weren't capable
of filling Duke's shoes.

33:45.649 --> 33:47.765
He'd be proud of you, you know.

33:48.527 --> 33:51.064
In fact, I bet he's up there right now

33:51.238 --> 33:54.071
eating roast beef and mashed potatoes
with the big guy,

33:54.241 --> 33:56.106
looking down on you and smiling.

33:58.078 --> 34:01.411
We're gonna do big things,
you and I.

34:02.707 --> 34:05.323
First, we gotta get you
some deputies.

34:06.294 --> 34:08.876
There's a new sheriff in town.

34:09.631 --> 34:12.589
And her name is Linda Esquivel.

34:22.978 --> 34:27.472
Uh, so I was wondering
if maybe we could

34:28.149 --> 34:31.391
keep what happened today
between us.

34:35.532 --> 34:37.363
You know, we all have secrets,
Junior.

34:37.576 --> 34:38.986
[CHUCKLES]

34:43.873 --> 34:45.955
You can call me James.

34:48.837 --> 34:52.329
I never did like being called Junior
anyways.

34:56.595 --> 34:58.506
I'm guessing you're a Scotch guy.

34:58.680 --> 35:00.170
You don't miss much, do you?

35:00.348 --> 35:02.464
Straight up, of course.

35:28.460 --> 35:30.325
Maybe we should do this
another time.

35:33.840 --> 35:35.296
It's a small town, son.

35:37.594 --> 35:38.959
And we all support the team.

35:45.477 --> 35:46.808
What was that about?

35:47.395 --> 35:49.511
Long story.

36:40.323 --> 36:42.939
What kind of trouble
you been getting into?

36:45.286 --> 36:46.867
NO trouble.

36:47.038 --> 36:50.246
I went down into the cement works
and tried to find a way out.

36:50.417 --> 36:51.998
Failed, huh?

36:53.336 --> 36:54.792
Yeah.

36:54.963 --> 36:57.170
The dome cuts straight through.

36:57.340 --> 36:58.625
Well, of course, it does.

36:58.800 --> 37:01.007
You didn't think it'd be that easy,
did you?

37:03.972 --> 37:05.633
What were you doing
with that Barbie guy?

37:05.807 --> 37:08.719
- Well, that's none Of your business.
- I'll make it my business.

37:09.477 --> 37:11.513
Not unless I tell you to.

37:12.021 --> 37:14.398
Don't you worry your head
over Barbie.

37:15.400 --> 37:18.016
Let the grown-ups do theirjob.

37:22.323 --> 37:25.315
Drink your milk now, Junior.

37:34.002 --> 37:37.494
- What are you doing?
- I don't know. Maybe I can fix it.

37:37.672 --> 37:38.912
Really?

37:39.090 --> 37:40.671
That thing blew up
like the Death Star.

37:40.842 --> 37:43.754
Yeah, but the Empire rebuilt the
Death Star in the Return of the Jedi.

37:43.928 --> 37:46.180
It was almost fully Operational.

37:46.723 --> 37:48.008
I like nerds.

37:48.183 --> 37:49.423
CAROLYN:
Norrie?

37:49.601 --> 37:52.468
- Oh, God.
- Norrie, are you here--?

37:54.230 --> 37:55.686
Carolyn, how did you find me?

37:55.857 --> 37:59.770
Something goes boom in a small town,
parents tend to know.

38:01.029 --> 38:02.235
Let's go.

38:03.114 --> 38:04.399
Who is this lady?

38:06.409 --> 38:09.492
- She's one of my moms.
- One of your--?

38:09.662 --> 38:13.246
Okay, I guess there's just some things
I didn't want you to know about me.

38:17.295 --> 38:21.584
But, hey, thanks
for almost getting beat up for me.

38:22.425 --> 38:25.758
That was kind of chivalrous.

38:26.679 --> 38:28.419
[ELECTRICITY SPARKS]

38:31.976 --> 38:33.227
- Oh, my God.
- What happened?

38:33.394 --> 38:35.225
CAROLYN:
Norrie? Norrie.

38:35.396 --> 38:37.887
- The pink stars are falling in lines.
- Norrie.

38:38.066 --> 38:39.931
[IN UNISON]
The pink stars are falling in lines.

38:40.109 --> 38:41.815
CAROLYN: Norrie.
- The pink stars are falling.

38:41.986 --> 38:43.726
CAROLYN: Norrie.
- The pink stars are falling.

38:43.905 --> 38:45.486
CAROLYN: Get help!
- The pink stars are falling.

38:45.657 --> 38:47.488
CAROLYN: Go!
- The pink stars are falling.

38:47.659 --> 38:49.320
[DOOR OPENS]

38:57.252 --> 38:58.458
Hey, Angie.

39:01.506 --> 39:03.087
Did you make it under?

39:03.258 --> 39:05.840
Uh-uh. Uh...

39:09.556 --> 39:11.763
There's no way out.

39:12.725 --> 39:14.886
I made sure of it.

39:17.063 --> 39:20.055
What happened to your hands?

39:21.109 --> 39:22.940
I beat on that thing.

39:25.822 --> 39:30.156
Stood up and beat on it
until the lights went out, Angie.

39:33.496 --> 39:35.612
Because I love you.

40:11.492 --> 40:13.869
So that comment that you made
about me running into the fire

40:14.037 --> 40:15.823
was aggravatingly hypocritical.

40:16.497 --> 40:18.408
NO, especially considering
the adventure

40:18.583 --> 40:20.995
you went on today with Big Jim.

40:21.169 --> 40:23.501
Yeah, but there's a difference
between me and you.

40:23.671 --> 40:25.047
How SO?

40:26.341 --> 40:29.299
I take Off after the fire's out.

40:30.053 --> 40:32.886
I mean, at least,
when there's somewhere to take Off to.

40:38.353 --> 40:40.139
You bruised your knuckles.

40:42.523 --> 40:45.105
Yeah, I bruised my knuckles.

40:46.444 --> 40:49.982
And you really were just passing
through Chester's Mill?

40:50.156 --> 40:51.896
NO connection
to anyone here in town?

40:54.327 --> 40:55.567
Nope.

40:59.123 --> 41:00.454
Good night, Julia.

41:04.212 --> 41:05.998
[DOOR CLOSES]

41:11.219 --> 41:12.709
[SHOWER RUNNING]
